 Parkwood Entertainment Logo
Parkwood Entertainment is an American management and entertainment company founded by Beyoncé Knowles-Carter in 2010. The company began as a production unit for videos and films in 2008. It was located in New York City until 2016, when its offices were moved to Los Angeles due to closer proximity to Beyoncé’s primary residence. Its involvements include products for music production, motion pictures and television specials related to Beyoncé. The company’s first release was the film Cadillac Records.
